features: Baby Pacifier - Natursutten's Medium Size natural rubber pacifiers are the perfect size for young infants and older babies 6-12 months. We also offer Small Size pacifiers for 0-6 months and Large Size pacis for 12 months and up. Need Pacifier Storage? Add our PaciPouch Pacifier Holder, 100% Organic Cotton and machine washable

Safer and Softer - Our pacifiers are made exclusively from pure natural rubber from Hevea Brasiliensis trees. They are free of BPA, phthalates, and chemical softening agents. Each natural rubber pacifier is naturally softer than silicone pacifiers and gentle on sensitive gums

Best Pacifier for Breastfed Babies - Ultimately, the best pacifier is the one your baby will take. We've found that better breastfeeding pacifiers feature a Round shield that gently rests upon baby's nose, which simulates breastfeeding. Similarly, a Round bulb nipple more closely mimics the natural breast, which reduces nipple confusion in breastfed babies

Supporting Healthy Teeth and Breathing - Your baby may instead prefer a butterfly pacifier shield that leaves a cut-out to let their nose be free to wriggle around and breathe! They might also prefer an Orthodontic pacifier nipple, which is flat on the bottom and reduces stress on baby's bottom teeth and jaw

One Piece Baby Pacifiers - Whichever binkie is right for your baby, all Natursutten pacifiers feature one-piece construction with no joints or cracks where dirt and other yucks can collect. They're also super easy to clean with mild soap and running water. Pediatricians recommend replacing a well-used or worn pacifier every 4-6 weeks.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: The 100% natural rubber line of pacifiers made in Italy. Natursutten pacifiers are made with all-natural rubber, with no BPA, phthalates, or chemical softening agents. The patented, one-piece design is free of joints or cracks where dirt can accumulate, and the pacifiers are easier to clean. Crafted in Italy by a family-run business, each Natursutten pacifier takes 7 weeks and 20 hand-held steps to go from liquid sap to finished product. Since the rubber from the Hevea Brasiliensis tree is softer than the silicone in mass-produced pacifiers, your baby will enjoy a gentler, more natural feel.

PACIFIERS SAFER BY DESIGN The first thing you’ll notice is the single-piece design. This means no joints or cracks where yucky things can hide, and it’s easy to wash by hand with just mild soap and warm water. Natursutten’s construction adheres to the strictest European and U.S. safety standards. Babies love our Natursutten pacifiers. One reason may be the soft rubber, which has a more natural feel than the artificial silicone used in mass- produced pacifiers. You’ll understand at first touch. NATURAL RUBBER Made from liquid rubber milk from sustainably harvested rubber trees.Natural rubber is softer than siliconeCrafted in Italy by a family-run business, each Natursutten pacifier takes 7 weeks and 20 hand-held steps to go from liquid sap to finished product.Natural rubber has no BPA, phthalates, or chemical softening agents. WHICH MODEL DO I CHOOSE? PaciPixy and PaciPouch contain no clips, buttons or other potential choking hazards - Keeping it a safe and soft addition; easy to hold on to and easy to find.

When you buy a Natursutten pacifier, you and your baby avoid Allergy-causing substancesArtificial colorsChemical softenersParabens, PVC, and phthalates Each pacifier is made from 100% natural rubber, simply better for your baby.

Original - round Original - orthodontic Butterfly - round Butterfly - orthodontic PaciPouch Breastfeeding Baby Preferred ✓ ✓ ✓ Eases Stress on New Teeth ✓ ✓ Extra-Comfy Nose Notch ✓ ✓ Ventilated for Easy Breathing ✓ ✓ ✓ ✓

ALL NATURAL Our commitment to a better Earth doesn’t end with the all-natural rubber in our pacifiers. Our packaging is printed with natural soy ink. Even the clear window is made of bio plastic—from corn, not petroleum.

The Natursutten Story Anne-Dorthe Schroeder started Natursutten (which means 'natural pacifier' in Danish) in 2006 when she couldn’t find a healthy option for her newborn son. “The media is full of stories about dangerous baby gear, recalls, and harmful plastics. As a new mother, I thought about how many hours my son was going to have a pacifier in his mouth, and I was determined to find a truly safe alternative. I felt I owed it to my child and other babies around the world – to do better.”

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect crib paci
reviews.reviewText: My baby took more to the round shape pacifiers over the orthodontic ones. He always loved the bibs pacis but would roll over on them and wake up. These are perfect because they are his preferred shape but the rubber material is soft so if he rolls on it in the night he rarely notices and we all sleep better! The medium size is similar to the up to 6 months bibs pacifiers. Expensive but very high quality. No smell and only needs just a little soap and water to clean.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 25, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best Pacifier on the market!
reviews.reviewText: We LOVE this paci! We have been using them for a little over a year now. We keep two in rotation at a time and they last us roughly two months before we need to change it out. I always keep four extra on hand, because sometimes I don’t realize it is time to get a new one and need to replace it right then. And, oh goodness if we lose one in the car or the bed at night... I have an extra on hand until we can really look for it. With a walker now, she may hide them too and we will find it in a boot a week later...lol! We upped the size when my baby was about 3 months old. It took her a couple days to adjust to the new size, so if we have anymore children, I may wait a few more months. This is not an issue for price point because this is one of the only expenses we have for babies. We cloth diaper, breastfeed, and buy everything but car seats second hand, so this is a very minimal expense of $12 (sometimes on sale for $9!) a month. I really appreciate this brand! Side note: We use the rounded and her teeth look perfectly fine. The only child we have a pallet issue with is our thumb sucker, so I am in the minority on pro paci. We have never had a pallet issue with our paci takers because by 1/2-2 they are off the paci and that is easier to take away than a thumb.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars baby loves it!
reviews.reviewText: My son has not been one for paci’s i have been through so many different kinds trying to find the one and haven’t. Until i found this brand! The moment i popped it into his mouth he started sucking away! The nipple size is absolutely perfect for him and expands with every sucking motion. At $12 and some change for a binky i did think it was very pricey for just one, but im very glad i spent the money because it’s worth every penny! The pacifier is so soft and flexible so i don’t have to worry about him rolling over on it and hurting himself in his crib. Overall i definitely love this product and will be buying another one for the diaper bag for sure! This one’s a game changer!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 27, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice natural good quality
reviews.reviewText: I like this binky. I like the fact that it was made natural and the fact that it is one piece. It is of good quality. The only thing is my baby didn't like it. She got use to her other binkys. This binky mouth piece is not flat like other binkys. It has a more rounded feel to it, and it doesn't flatten out in babys mouth. I wish she would have liked it because I did. It is a five star binky but I gave it 4 only because my baby didn't like it and it is on the pricey side. Im always looking for a good one piece binky because I don't like feeling like pieces can come apart. Its really hard to find a one piece for a baby 6 months plus.Update: 2 months after my first review. My baby loves this binky now. I guess it took her some time to get use to it, but she loves it. She uses it for a night time binky because I feel safer knowing she has a one piece at night when I'm not able to supervise her binky usage. I'm so glad she loves it, so I gave 5 stars.
Tolle Form, riecht nicht giftig, gut zu reinigen, richtig Klasse!!!

reviews.reviewTitle: Für uns der beste Schnuller! Endlich kein Plastik mehr!
reviews.reviewText: Wir lieben die Schnuller von Naturesutten! Bei unserem 3. Kind wollten wir endlich keine Kunststoffschnuller mehr! Das große Plastikproblem auf diesem Planeten beschäftigt uns immer mehr und das sollte es auch! Naturesutten Schnuller bestehen zu 100% aus Naturkautschuk. Sie liegen gut im Mund aber laden nicht zum Dauernuckeln ein, was ein riesen Vorteil ist. Wenn der junge Mann eingeschlafen ist, fällt der Schnuller raus und er schläft friedlich weiter. Die Schnuller bestehen aus 1en Stück und können nicht in Einzelteile verfallen. Sie lassen sich gut reinigen. Wir tauschen ihn etwa alle 6 Wochen aus, das stört uns aber nicht und ist definitiv kein Nachteil! Wir empfehlen sie immer weiter und sind echte Fans!
Ich bin sehr zufrieden mit dem Schnuller ich werde immer gerne kaufen
